From a60c8c0d7261edb04f03054f03fe6b5709102f25 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 07:08:33 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] core: Add DEVICE_INITIAL_SDK_INT to Build.VERSION

Android 12 (API 31) introduced DEVICE_INITIAL_SDK_INT in Build.VERSION.
Certain Zygisk modules, such as PlayIntegrityFix and Tricky Store,
attempt to read this field via reflection to spoof hardware attestation.

On Android 11 (API 30), this field does not exist, which causes these
modules to throw a java.lang.NoSuchFieldError, ultimately crashing
core system processes like com.android.vending (Play Store).

This patch adds DEVICE_INITIAL_SDK_INT and points it to FIRST_SDK_INT,
backporting the expected Android 12 API surface to prevent Zygisk
modules from triggering fatal crashes.

Change-Id: I4023b30e282880e460f30622991896ce6f72a7c2
Signed-off-by: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 core/java/android/os/Build.java | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/core/java/android/os/Build.java b/core/java/android/os/Build.java
index 8c6fca50fa8..38cc3a7fb5f 100755
--- a/core/java/android/os/Build.java
+++ b/core/java/android/os/Build.java
@@ -309,6 +309,15 @@ public class Build {
         public static final int FIRST_SDK_INT = SystemProperties
                 .getInt("ro.product.first_api_level", 0);
 
+        /**
+         * The SDK version of the software that <em>initially</em> shipped on
+         * this hardware device.
+         *
+         * @hide
+         */
+        @TestApi
+        public static final int DEVICE_INITIAL_SDK_INT = FIRST_SDK_INT;
+
         /**
          * The developer preview revision of a prerelease SDK. This value will always
          * be <code>0</code> on production platform builds/devices.
